<h1>Case 7 — Visitors Flow Analysis</h1>

<h2>Brief Description</h2>
<p>
The Visitors Flow Analysis system monitors real-time footfall and crowd movement across Velora’s 
public zones such as amusement parks, malls, beaches, and transport hubs. 
It predicts congestion, identifies high-density areas, and helps city authorities manage movement effectively.
</p>

<h2>Rising Problems</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Overcrowding in public spaces leading to safety risks.</li>
    <li>Sudden visitor surges during events causing traffic jams.</li>
    <li>Difficulty in predicting peak visiting times.</li>
    <li>Inefficient allocation of staff and resources during crowd formation.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Solutions / Logic Used</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Sliding Window Technique:</strong> Analyzes continuous visitor flow and detects sudden peaks.</li>
    <li><strong>Hash Maps:</strong> Stores sensor logs and footfall data for each zone.</li>
    <li><strong>BFS:</strong> Identifies how crowd spreads across connected areas.</li>
    <li><strong>Priority Queue (Heap):</strong> Finds top congested zones in real-time.</li>
    <li><strong>Queue:</strong> Manages sequential footfall entries and movement data streams.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Suitable SDGs</h2>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 11 — Sustainable Cities & Communities</strong>
    <p>Ensures safe public spaces through crowd regulation and mobility planning.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 3 — Good Health & Well-Being</strong>
    <p>Reduces safety hazards caused by overcrowding and improves emergency accessibility.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 9 — Industry, Innovation & Infrastructure</strong>
    <p>Promotes intelligent monitoring using algorithmic and sensor-based systems.</p>
</div>

